-- Toulouse Killer’s Brother Brought to Paris by Police, AFP Says
-- B y   H e l e n e   F o u q u e t
-- 2012-03-24T09:36:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-24/toulouse-killer-s-brother-brought-to-paris-by-police-afp-says.html
France ’s anti-terrorism judicial
police transferred the 29-year-old brother of the man who killed
seven people in Toulouse to Paris for more questioning, Agence
France-Presse reported, citing an unidentified source close to
the investigation.  Abdelkader Merah and his girlfriend will arrive in Paris
later today to be interrogated by anti-terror magistrates, AFP
said. According to French legislation, suspects held under anti-
terror rules can be held for up to 96 hours for questioning,
according to AFP.  Mohamed Merah, 23, killed three paratroopers, three
children and one teacher between March 11 and 19. He was shot
dead by the police on March 21.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Helene Fouquet in Paris at 
